1Machu Picchu is in Peru.
2The largest desert in the world is the Sahara, but if you count cold deserts, it’s the Antarctic Desert.
3The Great Barrier Reef is in Australia.
The highest waterfall in the world is Angel Falls in Venezuela.
The world’s largest rainforest is the Amazon Rainforest, and it’s in Brazil.
The capital city of Japan is Tokyo.
4The river that flows through Egypt is the Nile.
5Yellowstone National Park is in Wyoming, USA.
6The largest lake in Africa is Lake Victoria.
Venice is in Italy.
The tallest mountain in Africa is Mount Kilimanjaro, in Tanzania.
Canada has the most lakes in the world.
7The largest island in the Mediterranean Sea is Sicily.
8The capital city of New Zealand is Wellington.
9The ancient city of Petra is in Jordan.
10The river that runs through Paris is the Seine.
The Grand Canyon is in Arizona, USA.
